# Network Traffic Analysis Lab — ARP Spoofing Detection

## Overview
A self-built packet capture and analysis exercise using Python (Scapy)
instead of a packaged training platform. `generate_traffic.py` constructs
a small, realistic capture (ARP, DNS, TCP) entirely offline and writes it
to a `.pcap` file. `analyze_traffic.py` then reads that file and baselines
IP-to-MAC mappings from ARP replies, flagging any IP that's claimed by more
than one MAC address — the standard signature of ARP spoofing / cache
poisoning (the same logic tools like arpwatch and Wireshark's duplicate-IP
filter use).

## Files
- `generate_traffic.py` — builds the synthetic capture
- `analyze_traffic.py` — reads it and runs the detection
- `lab_traffic.pcap` — the generated capture (openable in real Wireshark)

## How to run it
```
python3 generate_traffic.py
python3 analyze_traffic.py
```

